{
  "texts": [
    "We specifically target the disruption of downstream tasks based on VAE encodings, such as diffusion models, rather than the VAEs' own reconstruction.",
    "Furthermore, we attack the distributional parameters (µ, σ 2) defining the approximate posterior q(z|x), rather than the sampled latent variables themselves.",
    "This allows us to explore vulnerabilities in VAEbased systems where distributional properties are critical for downstream processing.2) Attack on Diffusion-based Image Editing: Recent research has paid attention to adversarial attacks against diffusion models for image editing.",
    "[5] targeted the noise prediction module, while [6] and [33] minimized latent space distances.",
    "[7] combined semantic and textural losses for protection."
  ]
}